{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-classic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/basic-javascript/global-vs--local-scope-in-functions","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"basic-javascript","demoType":null,"title":"Globalni Naspram Lokalnog Opsega u Funkcijama","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Moguce je imati <dfn>lokalne</dfn> i <dfn>globalne</dfn> promenljive sa istim imenom. Kada se to desi, lokalna promenljiva ima prednost nad globalnom.</p>\n<p>U ovom primeru:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-js\">const someVar = \"Hat\";\n\nfunction myFun() {\n  const someVar = \"Head\";\n  return someVar;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Funkcija <code>myFun</code> vraca string <code>Head</code> jer postoji lokalna verzija promenljive.</p>\n</section>","id":"56533eb9ac21ba0edf2244c0","hasEditableBoundaries":false,"instructions":"<section id=\"instructions\">\n<p>Dodajte lokalnu promenljivu u funkciji <code>myOutfit</code> da prebrisete vrednost <code>outerWear</code> stringom <code>sweater</code>.</p>\n</section>","notes":null,"challengeType":1,"helpCategory":"JavaScript","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":18194,"hooks":null,"fields":{"slug":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/basic-javascript/global-vs--local-scope-in-functions"},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":false,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"scriptjs","ext":"js","name":"script","contents":"// Setup\nconst outerWear = \"T-Shirt\";\n\nfunction myOutfit() {\n  // Only change code below this line\n\n  // Only change code above this line\n  return outerWear;\n}\n\nmyOutfit();","head":null,"tail":null,"editableRegionBoundaries":[],"history":["script.js"]}],"saveSubmissionToDB":null,"tests":[{"text":"<p>Ne treba da menjate globalnu vrednost <code>outerWear</code>.</p>","testString":"assert(outerWear === 'T-Shirt');"},{"text":"<p><code>myOutfit</code> treba da vrati string <code>sweater</code>.</p>","testString":"assert(myOutfit() === 'sweater');"},{"text":"<p>Ne treba da menjate <code>return</code> naredbu.</p>","testString":"assert(/return outerWear/.test(__helpers.removeJSComments(code)));"}]}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/#basic-javascript","dashedName":"global-vs--local-scope-in-functions","certification":"javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures","disableLoopProtectTests":false,"disableLoopProtectPreview":false,"superBlock":"javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"basic-javascript","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/basic-javascript/understanding-undefined-value-returned-from-a-function","prevChallengePath":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/basic-javascript/local-scope-and-functions","id":"56533eb9ac21ba0edf2244c0","saveSubmissionToDB":null},"projectPreview":{"challengeData":{"challengeType":1,"challengeFiles":[{"name":"script","ext":"js","contents":"function rangeOfNumbers(startNum, endNum) {\n  if (endNum - startNum === 0) {\n    return [startNum];\n  } else {\n    const numbers = rangeOfNumbers(startNum, endNum - 1);\n    numbers.push(endNum);\n    return numbers;\n  }\n}","history":["script.js"],"fileKey":"scriptjs"}]}},"id":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/basic-javascript/global-vs--local-scope-in-functions"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3858520367"],"slicesMap":{}}